        use: "FOR evaluating effectiveness of conservation efforts: despite massive investment ($1.2 billion), the Reef continues to decline because the fundamental cause (global warming) is beyond Australia's control — a textbook case of local action being insufficient for global problems. FOR the economic argument for environmental protection: $6.4 billion annual contribution provides a clear utilitarian case. FOR international cooperation being essential: the Reef's fate depends on global emissions reductions, not Australian reef management — unilateral conservation is necessary but insufficient. COUNTER: framing the Reef as 'beyond saving without global action' risks fatalism — local interventions (crown-of-thorns starfish control, water quality improvement) do measurably help. COUNTER: the $6.4 billion economic framing reduces nature to its monetary value — the Reef has intrinsic ecological value independent of human economic benefit.",
